(2, 63, 'Eddie Stone', 'bural.pm@gmail.com', '', '77.247.22.124', '2017-04-13 07:00:58', '2017-04-13 07:00:58', 'Vincent was one of the first restaurants I discovered upon moving to New York last summer, and it remains a favorite. Despite its sizable menu full of pastas, sandwiches, and pizzas, I almost always get the same thing – the Vincent pizza. It\\\'s made with Ricotta &amp; Marinara sauces, spiced with oregano, and topped with eggplant, red onions, basil, Pecorino Romano &amp; Mozzarella. It really is one of the best pizzas I\\\'ve ever had – and I eat a lot of pizza.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(3, 63, 'Helen Dean', 'bindyuk.irina@gmail.com', '', '77.247.22.124', '2017-04-13 07:01:49', '2017-04-13 07:01:49', 'The pizza is delicious! The crust is thin and crispy, great sauce, and awesome cheese blend. And it makes a cute cheap date!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
