rtant;background-image: url(http://papyrus.wedoweb.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/img_1.jpg?id=358) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1541379817451{padding-right: 100px !important;padding-left: 100px !important;}\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Explore Exotic Foods\" font_container=\"tag:h1|text_align:left|color:%23121618\" use_theme_fonts=\"yes\" css=\".vc_custom_1541380328318{margin-top: 1px !important;margin-bottom: 43px !important;}\"][vc_single_image image=\"220\" img_size=\"full\" css=\".vc_custom_1489743761202{margin-bottom: 21px !important;}\"][vc_column_text]Egypt was at the crossroads of trade, and throughout its history, welcomed people from other cultures who brought along exotic cooking ingredients and preparation techniques. Fine desserts made with mastic and pistachios were surely the outcome of an open society that welcomed people from Europe and the Levant to call Egypt their home.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\"][vc_column css=\".vc_custom_1541380457387{border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"][pm_vc_custom_map custom_map_code=\"\" custom_map_height=\"470px\" custom_css=\".vc_custom_1541378192437{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home 1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '547-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-05 03:45:11', '2018-11-05 03:45:11', '', 547, 'http://papyrus.wedoweb.co/?p=1647', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
